<div class="about-tech">
	<h4 class="about-q">What's your technical background?</h4>
	<p>I first starting coding more than 15 years ago, when I taught myself HTML and CSS as an enthusiastic 11-year-old. Throughout high school and college, I spent countless hours building and designing (and then rebuilding and redesigning) websites as a hobby, occasionally dabbling in PHP and JavaScript when my ideas required it. </p>
	<p>In 2013, I decided to pursue web development as a profession. For the next two years, I spent all of my nights and weekends studying Ruby, Ruby on Rails, and a number of object-oriented programming languages to enhance my skillset. I earned a certificate in Ruby Programming from the University of Washington in 2014, and shortly thereafter I was hired as a junior developer for a small financial start-up just north of Chicago.</p>
	<p>On a daily basis, I now write new features and fix bugs across a Rails 3/CanJS/PostgreSQL stack. Because I quickly proved myself to be a reliable and fast-paced developer, my duties have increased significantly from the junior level in a short period of time, and I now regularly tackle independent feature development, project management, and UI/UX design. I still spend many nights and weekends staying up-to-date with the latest technologies and frameworks, which most recently have included Ember.js and Angular.js. Even as I sharpen those skills, I'm always looking for the new tools to experiment with and master.</p>
