<div class="about-education">
	<h4 class="about-q">What did you study in school?</h4>
	<p>I earned my B.A. in Women's Studies from the University of California, Riverside in 2009. I followed that up with a M.A. in Women's Studies in 2011 from San Diego State University. Though I'd initially planned to pursue a doctorate in sociology, I realized that my passion and interests no longer lied in academia, but in programming. In 2014, I began my career transition by earning a certificate in Ruby Programming from the University of Washington in August.</p>
</div>

<div class="about-care">
	<h4 class="about-q">What you care about?</h4>
	<p>As my B.A. and M.A. majors might suggest, I care deeply about social justice issues, particularly as they relate to gender, race, and sexuality. I still use and share this knowledge on a daily basis to promote awareness for women and minority issues within the tech world, whether it relates to the STEM pipeline, retention, or designing apps for more diverse audiences.</p>
	<p>Although I don't teach for a living, my previous experiences teaching undergraduate university courses have given me a deep appreciation for education, teaching, and pedagogy. I hope to use my teaching and public speaking skills to present talks at tech conferences in the near future.</p>
</div>

